# QZ Account Context

Account-specific IDs and resources. Copy this file to `account.md` (gitignored) and fill in your own values.

Discover your IDs by running `/qz-browser explore` or calling the relevant APIs.

## User
- Name: <your-name> (<username>-<institution_id>)
- User ID: `user-<your-user-id>`
- Institution ID: `<your-institution-id>`

## Workspaces

| Name | ID | Internet | Notes |
|------|-----|----------|-------|
| 分布式训练空间 | `ws-...` | no | H100/H200, primary for training |
| 可上网GPU资源 | `ws-...` | **yes** | 4090, internet-accessible GPU |
| CPU资源空间 | `ws-...` | **yes** | CPU only, online notebooks/SSH |

## All Known Pools

List the pools visible to your account. Use `qz pools` or the pool list API
to discover LCG IDs and node counts.

### Example workspace — shared GPU

| Pool name | LCG ID | GPU | VRAM | Nodes | Use |
|-----------|--------|-----|------|-------|-----|
| H200-3号机房 | `lcg-...` | H200 | 141GB | — | training / notebook |

## Projects

| Name | ID | Priority |
|------|-----|----------|
| my-project | `project-...` | 10 (HIGH) |

## Notebook Quota IDs

Quota IDs vary per workspace. Discover them via `GET /api/v1/notebook/schedule/{ws_id}`.

## Image Registry
- Internal (pull for training/notebooks): `docker.sii.shaipower.online/inspire-studio/`
- Push registry (for image upload): `docker-qb.sii.edu.cn/inspire-studio/`
